name: Planamarengo
description:
Macro photograph of a jumping spider, Planamarengo bimaculata. Incidentally the first record of this species outside South Africa. 
Skill: Medium (photography) + high (luck finding cool spiders, my speciality)
Time: 1/500 seconds? Or 1 hour taking blurry pics to get a few good ones and another hour to ID the spider.
Secrets: Spiders are awesome.
Comments: I love the hidden worlds macro photography can reveal. And I'm fortunate to live surrounded by interesting subjects!
